<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="17" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1437,505,1790]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,505,530]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Facial carina developed, arista long plumose, 
<number box="[845,859,505,529]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="4.0">4</number>
presutural and 
<number box="[1055,1069,505,529]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="4.0">4</number>
postsutural dorsocentral setae, abdominal tergites 
<number box="[369,383,542,566]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="3.0">3</number>
and 
<number box="[442,456,542,566]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="4.0">4</number>
with narrow transverse black bands not interrupted by pruinose band expanded from anterior portion.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="17" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1437,505,1790]" box="[199,630,613,638]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,372,613,638]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Redescription.</emphasis>
Body length 
<quantity box="[524,626,614,638]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.17" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" unit="mm" value="11.7">11.7 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1437,505,1790]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,346,649,674]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Male. Head.</emphasis>
Pale yellowish gray-white pruinosity, fronto-orbital plate more grayish; lunule yellow; antenna with scape and pedicel reddish yellow, flagellomere 
<number box="[753,767,686,710]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="1.0">1</number>
brown, arista yellow; palpus reddish yellow. Vertex about 
<number box="[151,200,722,746]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="0.23">0.23</number>
of head width; frontal vitta widened anteriorly, slightly more than twice width of fronto-orbital plate at middle; parafacial about 
<number box="[440,475,757,782]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="2.5">2.5</number>
times as wide as flagellomere 
<number box="[841,855,758,782]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="1.0">1</number>
at middle height; face rather well concave, facial carina developed, high and long, continuous to forwardly protruded lower margin of face, longer than antenna; genal height about 
<number box="[364,413,830,854]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="0.39">0.39</number>
of eye height; occiput weakly bulged. Inner vertical seta less than 
<number box="[1157,1167,830,854]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[1177,1192,830,854]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="2.0">2</number>
of eye height; ocellar seta 
<number box="[202,216,866,890]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="2.0">2</number>
/ 
<number box="[225,237,866,890]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="3.0">3</number>
as long as inner vertical seta; fronto-orbital plate with dense, fine short hairs which do not descend below level of lunule; lowest frontal seta nearly level of middle lunule. Antenna short, flagellomere 
<number box="[1209,1223,902,926]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="1.0">1</number>
about 
<number box="[1301,1336,902,926]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="2.8">2.8</number>
times as long as pedicel; arista short, slightly shorter than antenna, rather long plumose, total width including plumosity about 
<number box="[220,255,973,998]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="1.5">1.5</number>
times as wide as flagellomere. Palpus slightly widened at apex, about 
<number box="[1045,1080,973,998]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="1.5">1.5</number>
times as long as antenna.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1437,505,1790]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,294,1009,1034]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Thorax.</emphasis>
Black in ground color, postalar callus brown, scutum with dense pale yellowish gray-white pruinosity; 
<number box="[282,296,1046,1070]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="2.0">2</number>
rather broad and obscure outer longitudinal dark vittae on dorsum, which are widely separated by transverse suture, and 
<number box="[400,414,1082,1106]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="3.0">3</number>
narrow obscure inner vittae on anterior 
<number box="[861,871,1082,1106]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[881,897,1082,1106]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="2.0">2</number>
of presutural area; scutellum black on basal 
<number box="[1393,1404,1082,1106]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[1416,1431,1082,1106]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="3.0">3</number>
. Five to six postpronotal setae, 
<number box="[495,509,1118,1142]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="3.0">3</number>
basal setae arranged nearly in a straight line or median seta slightly set forward; 
<number box="[1422,1436,1118,1142]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="2.0">2</number>
presutural and 
<number box="[317,331,1154,1178]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="4.0">4</number>
postsutural acrostichal setae; 
<number box="[668,682,1154,1178]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="4.0">4</number>
presutural and 
<number box="[856,870,1154,1178]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="4.0">4</number>
postsutural dorsocentral setae; 
<number box="[1224,1238,1154,1178]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="3.0">3</number>
postsutural intraalar setae; 
<number box="[279,293,1190,1214]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="4.0">4</number>
supra-alar setae; 
<number box="[503,517,1190,1214]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="2.0">2</number>
katepisternal setae. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[756,828,1189,1214]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Wing.</emphasis>
Hyaline, tegula and basicosta black, lower calypter white. Relative lengths of 
<number box="[443,457,1225,1250]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="2.0">2</number>
nd, 
<number box="[499,511,1225,1250]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="3.0">3</number>
rd and 
<number box="[589,603,1225,1250]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="4.0">4</number>
th costal sectors approximately as 
<number box="[985,1002,1225,1250]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="2.0">2</number>
: 
<number box="[1006,1021,1225,1250]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="3.0">3</number>
: 
<number box="[1025,1066,1225,1250]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="1.5">1.5</number>
, vein M from dm-cu crossvein to its bend about twice distance between the bend and wing margin, bend of vein M with very short appendix. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,214,1297,1322]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Legs.</emphasis>
Black. Fore tibia with 
<number box="[481,495,1298,1322]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="2.0">2</number>
posterior setae; mid tibia with 
<number box="[854,868,1298,1322]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="3.0">3</number>
anterodorsal, 
<number box="[1031,1045,1298,1322]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="3.0">3</number>
posterodorsal and 
<number box="[1263,1277,1298,1322]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="2.0">2</number>
ventral setae; hind tibia with a row of closely set anterodorsal setae, 
<number box="[759,773,1334,1358]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="1.0">1</number>
posterodorsal and 
<number box="[984,1026,1334,1358]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="2.5" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="2.0">2–3</number>
ventral setae, strong submedian seta absent among row of anterodorsal setae. Fore claws and pulvilli shorter than 
<number box="[1013,1026,1369,1394]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="5.0">5</number>
th tarsomere.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1437,505,1790]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,323,1405,1430]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Abdomen.</emphasis>
Ovate, reddish brown on sides of tergites 
<number box="[798,864,1406,1430]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="3.0" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="2.0">2 to 4</number>
, dorsum with dense pale yellowish gray pruinosity on anterior 
<number box="[282,296,1442,1466]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="2.0">2</number>
/ 
<number box="[306,318,1442,1466]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="3.0">3</number>
of tergites 3, 3/ 
<number box="[500,513,1441,1466]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="5.0">5</number>
of tergite 
<number box="[632,646,1442,1466]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="4.0">4</number>
and 
<number box="[703,717,1442,1466]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="2.0">2</number>
/ 
<number box="[726,738,1442,1466]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="3.0">3</number>
of tergite 
<number box="[858,874,1441,1466]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="5.0">5</number>
, posterior transverse black band of tergites 
<number box="[1370,1436,1441,1466]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="4.0" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="3.0">3 to 5</number>
narrowed laterally and medially by pruinosity expanded from anterior pruinose portion. Hairs fine, dense, short and recumbent on dorsum of tergite 
<number box="[508,524,1514,1538]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="3.0">3</number>
, slightly sparser on tergite 
<number box="[824,838,1514,1538]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="4.0">4</number>
and finer and erect on tergite 
<number box="[1171,1187,1513,1538]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="5.0">5</number>
; syntergite 
<number box="[1315,1325,1514,1538]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="1.0">1</number>
+ 
<number box="[1343,1359,1514,1538]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="2.0">2</number>
with 
<number box="[1422,1436,1514,1538]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="1.0">1</number>
lateral marginal seta, without median marginal setae; tergite 
<number box="[828,842,1550,1574]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="3.0">3</number>
with 
<number box="[906,920,1550,1574]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="2.0">2</number>
short median marginal and lateral setae.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
